{"id": "glassforge-swade-core", "name": "SWADE Core Rules Reference Builds", "version": "1.1", "author": "Glassforge Games", "description": "All 47 vehicles from Savage Worlds core rulebook (pp.82-86). Weapon loadouts verified line-by-line against canon.", "vehicles": [{"name": "Bicycle", "size": -1, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Two wheels, no motor, no armour, no dignity. Half of all shots hit the rider instead.", "notes": "The bicycle is invisible. Nobody notices one more cyclist on a city street, which makes it the perfect surveillance and courier vehicle for low-tech campaigns. In chase scenes, she squeezes through gaps no car can follow \u2014 alleys, stairwells, crowded markets. 50% of shots hit the rider rather than the vehicle.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": -3, "handlingLevel": 0, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 16}, {"name": "Horse-Drawn Carriage", "size": 3, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Four wheels, one horse, variable passenger comfort. Stagecoaches, hansoms, and broughams all fall here.", "notes": "The carriage covers everything from open farm carts to enclosed broughams and four-horse stagecoaches. She's your chase vehicle for historical and fantasy campaigns \u2014 highway robberies, runaway horses, rooftop leaps onto the luggage rack. Variants include the fast but fragile hansom cab, the armoured prison wagon, and the heavy freight coach. Horse-drawn, so she stops when the horses do.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -3, "handlingLevel": -3, "woundsLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top", "towing"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 16}, {"name": "Early Automobile", "size": 3, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Crank-start, top-heavy, and terrifying at speed. Model Ts, Tin Lizzies, and their ilk.", "notes": "This covers the first generation of motor cars \u2014 Model Ts, Austin Sevens, Citro\u00ebn Type As, and their contemporaries. Slow, temperamental, and revolutionary. She puts your campaign on wheels for the first time: Prohibition rum-runners, early pulp adventures, the first getaway cars. Unreliable enough that a failed Repair roll at the worst possible moment is practically a genre convention.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -2, "handlingLevel": -2, "woundsLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "temperamental"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 40}, {"name": "Street Motorcycle", "size": 1, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Stock road bike \u2014 Harleys, Ducatis, or the local equivalent. Fast, exposed, and half the shots hit the rider.", "notes": "Stock road bikes from any era \u2014 Harley-Davidsons, Triumphs, Ducatis, BMWs, or Honda CBs depending on your setting. She splits lanes, threads traffic, and fits where cars can't follow. The rider is fully exposed \u2014 50% of shots hit them rather than the bike. That vulnerability is the price of agility. Consider whether your setting's bikers ride in gangs, because a pack of motorcycles in a chase changes the dynamic entirely.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 0, "woundsLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 1, "mphOverride": 120}, {"name": "Off-Road Motorcycle", "size": 0, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Knobby tyres, excellent suspension, questionable life choices. Trail bikes, enduros, and motocross machines.", "notes": "Trail bikes, enduros, motocross machines, and military despatch riders' mounts. She goes where roads don't \u2014 jungle recon, desert patrol, mountain courier runs. Think of everything from Steve McQueen's fence jump to modern special forces insertion by dirt bike. Treats each inch of Difficult Ground as 1.5 inches instead of 2 inches, same as four-wheel drive.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top", "all_terrain", "four_wd"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 80}, {"name": "Compact Car", "size": 4, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Economy hatchback. Honda Civics, Ford Fiestas, and a thousand forgettable commuter boxes.", "notes": "Every economy hatchback ever made \u2014 Honda Civics, Ford Fiestas, VW Golfs, Toyota Corollas. She's the default civilian vehicle. Every NPC drives one, every car park is full of them, every car chase starts or ends with one crumpled against a lamppost. Mechanically unremarkable, which is exactly the point \u2014 she's the baseline everything else is measured against.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 1, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 120}, {"name": "Mid-Size Sedan", "size": 4, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Four doors, air bags, reasonable legroom. Your Camrys, Accords, and fleet rental staples.", "notes": "Your Camrys, Accords, Passats, and fleet rental staples. She carries more passengers and gear than the compact, handles roughly the same, and blends into traffic just as easily. Also covers unmarked police cars, taxi cabs, and the anonymous saloon your players steal when they need to move without attracting attention. The world's most forgettable getaway car.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "cargo_bay"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 4, "mphOverride": 120}, {"name": "Family Minivan", "size": 4, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Sliding doors, cup holders, existential surrender. The vehicle of parenthood.", "notes": "Chrysler Voyagers, Toyota Previas, VW Transporters, and their kin. She carries a full party plus gear \u2014 the team vehicle for modern campaigns, the thing everyone piles into when the job goes sideways. Not fast, not tough, but she holds everyone and their equipment in one vehicle. Sliding side doors make boarding and exiting faster than a four-door sedan.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "cargo_bay"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 7, "mphOverride": 90}, {"name": "Sport Utility Vehicle", "size": 5, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Four-wheel drive, luxury features, poor fuel economy. Range Rovers to Cherokees.", "notes": "Range Rovers, Jeep Cherokees, Toyota Land Cruisers, Ford Explorers. She bridges civilian comfort and rough terrain capability. Four-wheel drive gets her off-road where sedans can't follow. The vehicle of choice for private military contractors, safari guides, rural law enforcement, and players who expect trouble outside city limits. Treats Difficult Ground as 1.5 inches per inch.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "four_wd", "all_terrain"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 7, "mphOverride": 120}, {"name": "Sports Car", "size": 4, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Two doors, low profile, speed over practicality. Mustangs, Camaros, and mid-life crises.", "notes": "Mustangs, Camaros, Porsches, Ferraris, Corvettes, and every mid-life crisis on four wheels. She wins chases through raw speed and sharp handling. Fast on straights, nimble in corners, and utterly useless off-road or in bad weather. The vehicle your players covet and the one that gets them into trouble. Two doors means getting into the back seat takes an action.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 3, "handlingLevel": 2, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 160}, {"name": "Semi-Truck", "size": 9, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Cab and trailer. Peterbilts, Kenworths, Scanias \u2014 the kings of the motorway.", "notes": "Peterbilts, Kenworths, Scanias, Volvos, and every long-haul cab that's ever jackknifed across a motorway. She can't manoeuvre, she can't hide, and she takes a long time to stop. But she carries anything, tows anything, and at highway speed she's an unstoppable battering ram. The trailer itself is roughly Size 7, Toughness 14(2) \u2014 big enough to serve as a mobile base or improvised roadblock.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "cargo_bay", "towing", "loud"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -4, "passengers": 1, "mphOverride": 75}, {"name": "WW2 Light Utility Vehicle", "size": 4, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Four-wheel drive workhorse. The Willys Jeep, Kubelwagen, and GAZ-67 kept armies moving.", "notes": "The Willys Jeep, Ford GPW, K\u00fcbelwagen, GAZ-67, and their Commonwealth equivalents. She goes everywhere and carries everything \u2014 reconnaissance, command vehicle, ambulance, weapons platform, officer's staff car. Open-topped and lightly armoured, which means the crew is always one burst away from disaster. The most versatile vehicle of the Second World War, and the ancestor of every military SUV since. Four-wheel drive.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "open_top", "four_wd"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 1, "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 65}, {"name": "WW2 Medium Tank (Allied)", "size": 8, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "The workhorse Allied tank. Shermans, Cromwells, and their equivalents \u2014 reliable, mass-produced, outgunned by late-war heavies.", "notes": "The M4 Sherman and its variants \u2014 the M4A1 with cast hull, the M4A3E8 'Easy Eight' with improved suspension, the Firefly with its 17-pounder gun. Also covers Cromwells, Crusaders, and other mid-war Allied designs. She wasn't the best tank of the war \u2014 late-war German armour outgunned her routinely \u2014 but there were always more of them. Use her as the reliable, available option that wins through numbers and logistics rather than individual superiority. Heavy Armor, Tracked.", "armourLevel": 2, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_75mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 30}, {"name": "WW2 Medium Tank (Soviet)", "size": 7, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Sloped front armour, rugged and simple. The T-34 and its derivatives defined the Eastern Front.", "notes": "The T-34 in all its variants \u2014 the T-34/76 with its original turret, the T-34/85 with the larger gun, and the countless field modifications that kept them fighting through Stalingrad and beyond. Her sloped armour was a revelation in 1941, deflecting shots that would have penetrated a flat-faced design. Simple enough to build in staggering numbers, rugged enough to operate in conditions that destroyed German machinery. Also covers the KV-1 series and other mid-war Soviet designs. Heavy Armor, Sloped Armor (front), Tracked.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 2, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_76mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 3, "mphOverride": 35}, {"name": "WW2 Medium Tank (Axis)", "size": 7, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "The backbone of Axis armoured divisions. Panzer IVs, StuGs, and their upgunned variants.", "notes": "The Panzer IV in its many marks \u2014 from the short-barrelled F1 to the long-gunned H and J variants. Also covers StuG III assault guns, Panzer IIIs, and Italian medium tanks like the M13/40. She's the backbone of Axis armoured divisions, not as famous as the Tiger or Panther but available in numbers and effective across the entire war. The opponent your players face most often in a European theatre campaign. Heavy Armor, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 3, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_75mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 4, "mphOverride": 25}, {"name": "WW2 Heavy Tank", "size": 8, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Massive, over-engineered, and terrifying. Tigers, IS-2s, and Pershings \u2014 the heavyweights that broke through and broke down.", "notes": "Tigers, King Tigers, IS-2s, Pershings, and Churchill heavies. The prestige vehicles of armoured warfare \u2014 slow, massively armoured, carrying the biggest guns of the war. The Tiger's 88mm could kill anything the Allies fielded at ranges they couldn't answer. Use heavies as boss encounters: the players hear one coming, plan around it, and need something clever because a frontal engagement is suicide. The King Tiger's reputation alone was a weapon. Heavy Armor, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 2, "armourLevel": 3, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_88mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "famous"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 25}, {"name": "Cold War Main Battle Tank", "size": 9, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Exported to half the world. T-72s, T-62s, and Chieftains \u2014 rugged, adequate, everywhere.", "notes": "T-72s in all their export variants, T-62s, Chieftains, AMX-30s, and the dozens of national variants that armed every Cold War proxy conflict. She shows up everywhere \u2014 Africa, the Middle East, South America, Southeast Asia. Not as capable as Western top-tier designs, but available, affordable, and dangerous enough that nobody wants to face one without anti-armour support. The most likely opponent in any post-1970 regional conflict. Heavy Armor, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 6, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_125mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg_modern", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -2, "mphOverride": 50}, {"name": "Modern Main Battle Tank (Eastern)", "size": 8, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Advanced fire control, composite armour, improved stabiliser. T-80s, T-90s, and Merkava IVs.", "notes": "T-80s, T-90s, and their upgraded variants with reactive armour, improved fire control, and autoloading 125mm guns. She represents the top tier of opposition for Cold War and modern campaigns \u2014 faster and lower-profile than Western equivalents, trading crew comfort for mechanical simplicity. The Merkava IV from Israel also fits this profile with its unique front-engine design. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 2, "armourLevel": 8, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_125mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg_modern", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -2, "mphOverride": 43}, {"name": "Cold War Wheeled APC", "size": 6, "loco": "wheeled", "desc": "Eight wheels, amphibious, cramped. BTR-series, Strykers, and Piranhas \u2014 gets troops there alive, mostly.", "notes": "BTR-60s, BTR-70s, BTR-80s, Strykers, Piranhas, Fuchs, and the dozens of eight-wheeled troop carriers that moved infantry across Cold War Europe and every conflict since. She swims rivers without preparation, which changes the tactical map entirely \u2014 obstacles that stop wheeled vehicles don't stop a BTR. Cramped, noisy, and the infantry inside can't wait to dismount. Amphibious, 4WD, Heavy Armor.", "toughLevel": 2, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "hmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "amphibious", "four_wd"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 1, "passengers": 8, "mphOverride": 49, "armourLevel": 1}, {"name": "Hover Tank", "size": 7, "loco": "hover", "desc": "Grav-drive heavy armour with energy weapons. No terrain penalties, no mercy.", "notes": "The next generation of armoured warfare \u2014 grav-drive heavy armour that ignores terrain entirely. She crosses rivers, rubble fields, and swampland at full speed. No tracks to throw, no mines to trigger, no terrain penalties whatsoever. The trade-off is she can't dig in \u2014 a hover vehicle fights on the move or not at all. Use her in science fiction settings where ground warfare has evolved past tracks and wheels. Heavy Armor, Hover, Night Vision.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 7, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "laser_heavy", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "laser_gat", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 3, "mphOverride": 45}, {"name": "Hover APC", "size": 7, "loco": "hover", "desc": "Grav-drive troop transport. Fast, sealed, carries a platoon over any surface.", "notes": "Grav-drive troop transport for science fiction settings. She delivers a full platoon across any terrain at speed \u2014 rivers, rubble, sand, ice, all the same to a hover drive. The future of mechanised infantry, where the terrain between drop point and objective is no longer a factor in mission planning. Heavy Armor, Hover.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 3, "speedLevel": 2, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "laser_gat", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 1, "passengers": 14, "mphOverride": 75}, {"name": "Civilian Biplane", "size": 4, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Open cockpit, fabric wings, a romantic way to die. Barnstormers, crop dusters, and Tiger Moths.", "notes": "Tiger Moths, Sopwith Pups, Stearman PT-17s, de Havilland Gipsy Moths, and every barnstormer that ever terrified a county fair. Open cockpit, fabric over wood and wire, and a top speed that lets passengers appreciate the scenery whether they want to or not. She's your inter-war and pulp adventure aircraft \u2014 slow enough for pistol fights from the cockpit, low enough to barnstorm, fragile enough that every bullet matters. Wind in your face, oil on your goggles, and the ground uncomfortably close.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": -2, "handlingLevel": 1, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top", "short_range"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 125}, {"name": "Light Civilian Aircraft", "size": 5, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Single-engine four-seater. Cessnas, Pipers, and Beechcrafts \u2014 the most common aircraft in the sky.", "notes": "Cessna 172 Skyhawks, Piper Cherokees, Beechcraft Bonanzas, and their hundreds of variants. The most common aircraft type in the sky. She's the plane your players charter, steal, or escape in \u2014 simple to fly, cheap to hire, and she lands on dirt strips that would destroy anything bigger. Also covers bush planes, survey aircraft, and the small charter services that connect remote locations to civilisation.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -2, "handlingLevel": 1, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 140}, {"name": "Civilian Helicopter", "size": 7, "loco": "vtol", "desc": "General-purpose rotorcraft. Bell 206s, Robinson R44s \u2014 news, medevac, tourism, escape.", "notes": "Bell 206 JetRangers, Robinson R44s, Eurocopter EC135s, and the hundreds of civilian rotorcraft types used for news coverage, executive transport, medevac, law enforcement, and tourism. Her unique ability is hover and vertical landing \u2014 she doesn't need a runway. Use her for dramatic rooftop extractions, medical evacuations, and the moment the players realise that the villain's escape plan doesn't involve roads. VTOL.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 0, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "stol"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 130}, {"name": "Executive Jet", "size": 8, "loco": "jet", "desc": "Fast, comfortable, and proof that someone is doing well. Learjets, Gulfstreams, Citations.", "notes": "Learjet 45s, Gulfstream IVs, Cessna Citations, Bombardier Challengers, and every private aircraft that costs more than most houses. She gets people across continents in hours, and her presence at an airstrip tells you everything about the owner \u2014 money, connections, urgency. She's also a beautiful target sitting unguarded on a remote runway at three in the morning.", "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 3, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "spacious", "long_range"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -3, "passengers": 10, "mphOverride": 540}, {"name": "Space Shuttle", "size": 13, "loco": "jet", "desc": "Reusable orbital vehicle. Three main engines, two solid boosters, one fragile heat shield.", "notes": "The NASA Space Shuttle, Buran, and their fictional successors. She demonstrates that size and Toughness don't always correlate with combat power \u2014 the shuttle is enormous but fragile, a precision instrument designed for a specific mission rather than a fight. Use her as a reference point for near-future and hard sci-fi campaigns where getting to orbit is still dangerous and expensive.", "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 5, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "sealed", "pressurised"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -19, "passengers": 40, "mphOverride": 17000}, {"name": "WW2 Heavy Bomber", "size": 10, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Four engines, ten crew, bristling with defensive guns. B-17s, Lancasters, and He-111s \u2014 strategic bombing incarnate.", "notes": "B-17 Flying Fortresses, B-24 Liberators, Avro Lancasters, Halifax bombers, He-111s, and the other strategic bombers that brought the war to the enemy's homeland. Ten crew, defensive guns at every angle, and hours of straight-and-level flying through flak corridors and fighter screens. Every mission is a survival horror session at 25,000 feet. Use her for crew-based scenarios where every position matters and a single engine fire can kill everyone aboard.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -4, "handlingLevel": -1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "turret", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "turret", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "bombs_ww", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "long_range"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 5, "mphOverride": 115}, {"name": "WW2 Fighter (Axis)", "size": 6, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Single-seat, single-engine interceptor. Bf-109s, Fw-190s, and Macchis dominated early-war skies.", "notes": "Bf-109s from the Emil through the Gustav and Kurf\u00fcrst marks, Fw-190 W\u00fcrgers, Macchi C.202 Folgores, and Kawasaki Ki-61 Hiens. The Axis built fast, well-armed interceptors with excellent climb rates and devastating cannon armament. The Bf-109 alone fought from Spain in 1937 to Berlin in 1945 \u2014 more were built than any other fighter in history. She's the opposition your players face in every European and North African air combat scenario.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "cannon_20mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 380}, {"name": "WW2 Fighter (Allied, Late-War)", "size": 7, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Long-range escort fighter. Mustangs, Thunderbolts, and Tempests \u2014 six-plus guns and the legs to use them.", "notes": "P-51 Mustangs in all their marks, P-47 Thunderbolts, Hawker Tempests, Lavochkin La-7s, and Yakovlev Yak-3s. The late-war Allied fighters that turned air superiority from a contest into a foregone conclusion. The Mustang's combination of range, speed, and firepower made her the complete package \u2014 escort bombers to Berlin and back, dogfight anything the Luftwaffe sent up, strafe ground targets on the return leg. Six or more guns and the fuel to use them.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}], "specials": ["enclosed", "long_range"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 437}, {"name": "WW2 Fighter (Pacific)", "size": 6, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Exceptional range and manoeuvrability, paid for with zero armour protection. Zeros, Oscars, and their kin.", "notes": "Mitsubishi A6M Zeros, Nakajima Ki-43 Oscars, Ki-84 Hayates, and the other Japanese fighters that traded protection for performance. Exceptional range and manoeuvrability, paid for with minimal armour and no self-sealing fuel tanks. A Zero could outmanoeuvre anything the Allies flew in 1942 \u2014 but one burst of .50 calibre could set her on fire. The ultimate glass cannon. Use her to show players that the best dogfighter in the sky can still die to a single lucky hit.", "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "cannon_20mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 350}, {"name": "WW2 Fighter (Allied, Early-War)", "size": 6, "loco": "turboprop", "desc": "Eight machine guns, elliptical wings, and the Battle of Britain. Spitfires, Hurricanes, and P-40s.", "notes": "Supermarine Spitfires (Mk I through V), Hawker Hurricanes, Curtiss P-40 Warhawks, Grumman F4F Wildcats, and the other Allied fighters that held the line before the war turned. The Spitfire and Hurricane split the Battle of Britain between them \u2014 Hurricanes took the bombers, Spitfires took the escorts. The P-40 fought in every theatre from North Africa to China. These aircraft weren't always the fastest or best-armed, but they were there when it mattered and the pilots who flew them refused to lose.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 1}], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 360}, {"name": "Modern Attack Helicopter", "size": 8, "loco": "vtol", "desc": "Tandem cockpit, chain gun, guided missiles. Apaches, Hinds, and Tigers \u2014 the apex predators.", "notes": "AH-64 Apaches in all their variants, Mi-24 Hinds, Mi-28 Havocs, Eurocopter Tigers, Mangusta A129s, and Kamov Ka-52 Alligators. Tandem cockpit, sensor suite, guided missiles, and an autocannon or chain gun that follows the gunner's helmet. She finds targets, kills them at range, and relocates before ground fire can respond. The Hind pioneered the concept, the Apache perfected it. Use her to demonstrate the terrifying capability gap between infantry and modern air power. Helicopter, Night Vision.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "autocannon_30mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hellfire", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -3, "mphOverride": 225}, {"name": "VTOL Strike Fighter", "size": 7, "loco": "vtol", "desc": "Vertical takeoff, subsonic, ground attack specialist. Harriers, Yak-38s, and their successors.", "notes": "AV-8B Harrier IIs, Sea Harriers, Yak-38 Forgers, and their successor concepts. She operates from roads, forest clearings, and amphibious ships too small for conventional aircraft. VTOL capability means close air support can stage from positions the enemy doesn't expect \u2014 and recover to locations they can't find. Slower than conventional jets, but she doesn't need a runway, and that changes everything. VTOL.", "speedLevel": 3, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "autocannon_25mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "sidewinder", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "bombs_mod", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["enclosed", "stol"], "customSpecial": "", "mphOverride": 630}, {"name": "Modern Air Superiority Fighter", "size": 9, "loco": "jet", "desc": "Twin-engine, Mach 2.5, designed to own the sky. Eagles, Flankers, Typhoons, and Rafales.", "notes": "F-15 Eagles, F-22 Raptors, Eurofighter Typhoons, Dassault Rafales, Saab Gripens, and their equivalents. Twin-engine, Mach 2+ capable, designed to own the sky from visual range to beyond-visual-range. The F-15 has never been shot down in air-to-air combat. The F-22 was built to ensure that record continues. She's the thing your players hear about but never want to see on the wrong side. Night Vision.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 3, "handlingLevel": 3, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "cannon_20mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "sidewinder", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "sparrow", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -4, "mphOverride": 1875}, {"name": "Modern Multirole Fighter (Eastern)", "size": 9, "loco": "jet", "desc": "Long-range interceptor. Flankers, Fulcrums, and their export derivatives.", "notes": "Su-27 Flankers, Su-30s, Su-35s, MiG-29 Fulcrums, and their export derivatives. The Soviet and Russian answer to Western air superiority \u2014 arguably more manoeuvrable at close range, equipped with excellent missiles, and exported to dozens of air forces worldwide. The Flanker family keeps evolving and keeps being dangerous. She represents peer-level opposition for any modern air combat campaign. Night Vision.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 2, "handlingLevel": 2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "autocannon_30mm", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "sidewinder", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "sparrow", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -4, "mphOverride": 1550}, {"name": "Vietnam-Era Utility Helicopter", "size": 7, "loco": "vtol", "desc": "The sound of the rotors IS the war. Hueys, Pumas, and Mi-8s \u2014 the workhorse of every conflict since.", "notes": "UH-1 Hueys, UH-60 Black Hawks, SA 330 Pumas, Mi-8 Hips, and the utility helicopters that defined warfare from Vietnam to Afghanistan. The Huey's distinctive two-blade rotor beat is the soundtrack of an entire war. She carries troops, evacuates wounded, delivers supplies, provides door-gun fire support, and defines the helicopter warfare era. Every variant from medevac to gunship started with this airframe. Helicopter.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 3, "passengers": 12, "mphOverride": 120}, {"name": "Age of Sail Warship", "size": 14, "loco": "water_sail", "desc": "Three masts, multiple gun decks, the capital ship of the age of sail. Galleons, men-o-war, and ships of the line.", "notes": "The seventy-four \u2014 the definitive warship of the age of sail. Two gun decks, a crew of five hundred, and enough iron in a single broadside to reduce an enemy to matchwood. The lower deck mounts the heaviest guns (24-32 pounders), the upper deck the workhorse 18-pounders, and the upper works bristle with lighter pieces for sweeping enemy decks. Broadside combat is her purpose \u2014 she doesn't chase, she dominates the space she occupies. Heavy Armor.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -1, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "heavy_cannon_bp", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 3}, {"weaponId": "med_cannon_bp", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 3}, {"weaponId": "light_cannon_bp", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 3}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 80, "mphOverride": 9}, {"name": "Ancient War Galley", "size": 13, "loco": "water_sail", "desc": "Oars and sails. Triremes, biremes, and dromons \u2014 ram the enemy, board the wreckage.", "notes": "Greek triremes, Roman quinqueremes, Byzantine dromons, Carthaginian war galleys, and Viking longships at the larger end. Oars give her independence from wind \u2014 she moves when and where the captain commands, which made galleys the dominant naval platform from Salamis to Lepanto. Her ram is as dangerous as her mounted weapons, and boarding actions were the decisive tactic of ancient naval warfare. Heavy Armor, Oars+Sails.", "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "ballista", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "ram_plate"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 100, "mphOverride": 20}, {"name": "Hydrofoil", "size": 10, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Foil-borne at speed, hull-borne at rest. Fast and smooth in calm water, miserable in rough.", "notes": "Boeing Jetfoils, Soviet Kometa class, Rodriquez RHS series, and military hydrofoils like the Pegasus class. She lifts out of the water on submerged foils at speed, dramatically reducing drag. Fast and smooth in calm water, increasingly uncomfortable as seas build. Your fast coastal patrol and intercept vessel \u2014 faster than conventional boats, more agile, and harder to hit when she's foil-borne.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 2, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -4, "passengers": 9, "mphOverride": 70}, {"name": "River Patrol Boat", "size": 7, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Shallow draft, heavy weapons, brown-water navy. PBRs, Swift Boats, and their equivalents.", "notes": "PBRs (Patrol Boat, River), Swift Boats (PCF), Nasty-class patrol boats, and their equivalents from every riverine conflict. Shallow draft, heavy weapons, brown-water navy. She navigates waterways that would ground larger craft, armed enough to suppress fire from both banks simultaneously. Think Mekong Delta, Colombian rivers, African estuaries \u2014 anywhere the war is fought on water too shallow for real warships. Heavy Armor.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 0, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 1}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 3, "mphOverride": 32}, {"name": "WW2 Torpedo Boat", "size": 12, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Fast, wooden, expendable. PT boats, E-boats, and MTBs \u2014 torpedo runs under fire.", "notes": "American PT boats, British MTBs (Motor Torpedo Boats), German E-boats (Schnellboote), Italian MAS boats, and Japanese torpedo craft. Fast, wooden-hulled, expendable. She closes with the enemy at speed, launches torpedoes, and runs before the return fire connects. Small crew, high risk, enormous potential if the torpedoes hit. JFK commanded PT-109. The SAS used them for commando raids. Every navy built them because they were cheap enough to risk and deadly enough to matter.", "toughLevel": -1, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": 1, "handlingLevel": 3, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "torpedo_ww", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "torpedo_ww", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "torpedo_ww", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "torpedo_ww", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -10, "mphOverride": 40}, {"name": "Rowboat", "size": 0, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Two oars, no motor, unlimited splinters. Dinghies, skiffs, and anything you can row.", "notes": "Dinghies, skiffs, ship's boats, tenders, coracles, and anything propelled by oars or poles. She's your silent insertion vehicle \u2014 invisible against a dark shoreline, carrying a small team to wherever they need to be without alerting anyone. Also the thing standing between your players and drowning when the ship goes down. Every nautical campaign needs half a dozen of these available at inconvenient moments.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": -3, "handlingLevel": -3, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top", "shallow_draft"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 5}, {"name": "Speed Boat", "size": 4, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Outboard motor, fibreglass hull, weekend fun. Ski boats, bass boats, and cigarette racers.", "notes": "Ski boats, bass boats, cigarette racers, RIBs (Rigid Inflatable Boats), and every fibreglass hull with an outboard motor. She's the sports car of the water \u2014 fast, agile, and fragile. Drug runners, coast guard pursuit, waterfront chases, and players who need to be somewhere coastal in a hurry. The cigarette boat variant is practically a genre requirement for any 1980s Miami campaign.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -2, "speedLevel": 2, "handlingLevel": 1, "woundsLevel": -2, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["open_top"], "customSpecial": "", "passengers": 3, "mphOverride": 90}, {"name": "Small Yacht", "size": 8, "loco": "water_turbo", "desc": "Comfortable coastal cruiser. Forty feet of fibreglass, teak, and someone else paying the marina fees.", "notes": "Beneteau Oceanis, Jeanneau Sun Odyssey, Bavaria Cruiser, and the dozens of 35-45 foot coastal cruisers that fill every marina. She's a location, not a chase vehicle. The party happens here, the deal goes down here, the villain entertains guests on the upper deck while your players infiltrate from the waterline. Comfortable, expensive, and conspicuous \u2014 nobody sails a yacht anonymously.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": -1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 1, "mods": {}, "weapons": [], "specials": ["enclosed", "spacious", "long_range"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -4, "passengers": 9, "mphOverride": 35}, {"name": "WW2 Light Tank", "size": 7, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Fast reconnaissance armour. Stuarts, Luchs, and T-70s \u2014 light gun, light armour, big heart.", "notes": "Stuarts, Luchs, T-70s, M3 Honeys, Tetrarchs, and their reconnaissance-role equivalents. Fast, undergunned, and used for scouting rather than direct engagement. She finds the enemy, reports back, and calls in the heavies. Players driving light tanks should feel the tension of bringing a small gun to a big fight \u2014 but also the advantage of speed when the shooting starts and they need to relocate. Heavy Armor, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 0, "armourLevel": 2, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_37mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 3, "mphOverride": 36}, {"name": "Modern Main Battle Tank", "size": 9, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Composite armour, thermal sights, stabilised gun. Abrams, Challenger 2, Leopard 2 \u2014 the Western benchmark.", "notes": "Abrams M1A1 and M1A2 variants, Challenger 2s, Leopard 2A6s, Leclercs, and Merkava IVs. The modern benchmark \u2014 composite armour that shrugs off most anti-tank weapons, thermal sights that see through darkness and smoke, stabilised guns that fire accurately at speed. She dominates open terrain absolutely. Use her to show players what modern military hardware can do, and to remind them that even the best tank is vulnerable in cities, forests, and mountains. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 2, "armourLevel": 8, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "tank_gun_120mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "hmg_modern", "mount": "pintle", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": -1, "mphOverride": 40}, {"name": "Modern Infantry Fighting Vehicle", "size": 7, "loco": "tracked", "desc": "Autocannon, anti-tank missiles, carries a full squad. Bradleys, Warriors, and BMPs.", "notes": "Bradleys, Warriors, BMPs, Marders, CV90s, and their equivalents. Not a taxi \u2014 she fights alongside the infantry she carries. Autocannon turret shreds light vehicles, anti-tank missiles threaten heavier armour, and the squad in the back dismounts through the rear ramp when the shooting starts. Players either ride in her or face her, and both experiences should feel dangerous. Heavy Armor, Night Vision, Tracked.", "toughLevel": 1, "armourLevel": 1, "speedLevel": 0, "handlingLevel": 0, "mods": {}, "weapons": [{"weaponId": "autocannon_25mm", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "mmg_modern", "mount": "turret", "linked": 0}, {"weaponId": "tow_missile", "mount": "fixed", "linked": 0}], "specials": ["heavy_armor", "enclosed", "night_ops"], "customSpecial": "", "crewLevel": 2, "passengers": 7, "mphOverride": 40}]}